            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h2 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1570807929653-minds-master-s-scholarships-for-indigenous-students" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#7be531a2-71b1-47c4-bffb-6070de5cb2ab" href="#accordion-content-1570807929653-minds-master-s-scholarships-for-indigenous-students" aria-controls="accordion-content-1570807929653-minds-master-s-scholarships-for-indigenous-students" aria-expanded="false">
                            MINDS Master’s Scholarships for Indigenous Students
                        </a>
                    </h2>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1570807929653-minds-master-s-scholarships-for-indigenous-students" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1570807929653-minds-master-s-scholarships-for-indigenous-students">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1570807929653 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="8f56e264-4356-4f68-9618-77f1b2dfbf35" >

    <p>Special Call for Applications: MINDS Master’s Scholarships for Indigenous Students<br> Second Call for Applications</p> 
<p><a href="http://www.sshrc-crsh.gc.ca/funding-financement/programs-programmes/dnd-minds-eng.aspx">Department of National Defence MINDS Scholarship Initiative<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></p> 
<p><strong>Application deadline: October 29, 2019 (8:00 p.m. eastern)</strong></p> 
<p><strong>Context<u></u></strong></p> 
<p>As part of a joint initiative with the Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council (SSHRC), the Department of National Defence (DND) is offering master’s-level scholarships to recipients of a SSHRC-funded Canada Graduate Scholarships—Master’s award who self-identify as Indigenous and whose work is related to the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/department-national-defence/programs/minds/defence-policy-challenges.html">Mobilizing Insights in Defence and Security (MINDS) Policy Challenges<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>&nbsp;and/or Canada’s defence policy,&nbsp;<a href="http://dgpaapp.forces.gc.ca/en/canada-defence-policy/docs/canada-defence-policy-report.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span><em>Strong, Secure, Engaged</em><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>.<u></u></p> 
<p><strong>Scholarship Value:&nbsp;</strong>$17,500<u></u></p> 
<p><strong>Note</strong>: The MINDS Master’s Scholarship for Indigenous Students may be held simultaneously with a Canada Graduate Scholarships—Master’s (CGS M) award.<u></u></p> 
<p><strong>Scholarship Duration:&nbsp;</strong>One year<strong><u></u></strong></p> 
<p><strong>Eligibility<u></u></strong></p> 
<p>To apply for a MINDS Master’s Scholarship for Indigenous Students, the applicant must:<u></u></p> 
<ul> 
 <li><u></u>be a SSHRC-funded CGS M award holder selected through the December 2018 competition;</li> 
 <li>self-identify as Indigenous; and be working in research areas that are related to the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/department-national-defence/programs/minds/defence-policy-challenges.html">MINDS Policy Challenges<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a><span>&nbsp;and/or Canada’s defence policy,&nbsp;</span><a href="http://dgpaapp.forces.gc.ca/en/canada-defence-policy/docs/canada-defence-policy-report.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span><em>Strong, Secure, Engaged</em><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a><span>.</span></li> 
</ul> 
<p><strong>Research Areas</strong></p> 
<p><u></u>For details on the research areas relevant to the MINDS Scholarship Initiative, applicants should consult:<u></u></p> 
<ul> 
 <li><u></u>the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/department-national-defence/programs/minds/defence-policy-challenges.html">MINDS Policy Challenges<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>, which represent key issue areas where DND and the Canadian Armed Forces (CAF) could benefit from external expertise to challenge or complement their thinking, and<u></u></li> 
 <li>Canada’s defence policy,&nbsp;<a href="http://dgpaapp.forces.gc.ca/en/canada-defence-policy/docs/canada-defence-policy-report.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span><em>Strong, Secure, Engaged</em><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>Examples of research areas that could be considered for funding under this initiative&nbsp;<strong>include, but are not limited to</strong>, the following: recruitment and retention; diversity in the CAF; hybrid warfare; defence and security cooperation; cyber and space domains; emerging technologies; geopolitics; international defence relations; peacekeeping and peace support operations; Arctic security; and the defence and security implications of climate change.<u></u></p> 
<p>Critical research perspectives, which may challenge or invite a reformulation of the policy themes and terms outlined in the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/department-national-defence/programs/minds/defence-policy-challenges.html">MINDS Policy Challenges<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="http://dgpaapp.forces.gc.ca/en/canada-defence-policy/docs/canada-defence-policy-report.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>Canada’s defence policy<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>, are welcome.<u></u></p> 
<p>The&nbsp;<a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/department-national-defence/programs/minds.html">MINDS program<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>, of which the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sshrc-crsh.gc.ca/funding-financement/programs-programmes/dnd-minds-eng.aspx">MINDS Scholarship Initiative<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>&nbsp;is a part, is committed to reflecting key Government of Canada priorities in the work it delivers, ensuring the incorporation of&nbsp;<a href="https://cfc-swc.gc.ca/gba-acs/index-en.html">Gender-Based Analysis Plus (GBA+)<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>. GBA+ requires the incorporation of diverse viewpoints. This means that deliberate efforts should be made to mitigate unintended bias related to intersecting identity factors (including, but not limited to, age, gender, ethnicity, race, disability, religion and geographic region). Applying a GBA+ lens to research ensures the problem is considered from multiple perspectives, supporting more inclusive research questions and results.<u></u></p> 
<p><strong>Application Process<u></u></strong></p> 
<p>Applicants who meet the eligibility requirements must submit a personal statement and a statement of thematic relevance in a single PDF document via SSHRC’s <a href="https://competitions.sshrc-crsh.gc.ca/500017/default.aspx">secure submission site<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>.<u></u></p> 
<ul> 
 <li><u></u>In their personal statement (maximum 500 words), applicants must describe how their experience as a member of an Indigenous community and their existing connection, or efforts to develop or re-establish a link, with that community have shaped and will inform their proposed research project.<u></u></li> 
 <li>In their statement of thematic relevance (maximum 250 words), applicants must describe how their proposed research project is related to one or more of the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/department-national-defence/programs/minds/defence-policy-challenges.html">MINDS Policy Challenges<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>&nbsp;and/or Canada’s defence policy,&nbsp;<a href="http://dgpaapp.forces.gc.ca/en/canada-defence-policy/docs/canada-defence-policy-report.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span><em>Strong, Secure, Engaged</em><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>.<u></u></li> 
</ul> 
<p><strong>Note</strong>: To apply to this funding opportunity, applicants will be asked to self-identify as Indigenous. They will also be asked to consent to this information being used by SSHRC and shared with DND as part of their application to the MINDS Master’s Scholarships for Indigenous Students. To facilitate subsequent communications between DND and applicants, SSHRC will also request applicants’ consent to share their personal contact information with DND.</p> 
<p><strong>Application Review Process</strong></p> 
<p>SSHRC staff will review personal statements and statements of thematic relevance to ensure that candidates have provided the requested information, in line with the instructions outlined in the “Application Process” section (above). Upon validating the alignment of candidates’ statements with the instructions, SSHRC will forward eligible applications to DND for a relevance review and ranking. SSHRC will not share candidates’ personal statements with DND.<u></u></p> 
<p>MINDS Master’s Scholarships for Indigenous Students will be offered to eligible candidates whose proposals are deemed by DND to be the most relevant to its research areas. The awards will be offered to the limit of available funding.<u></u></p> 
<p><strong>Contact Information<u></u></strong></p> 
<p>For more information, contact:<u></u></p> 
<p><strong>Email:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="mailto:fellowships@sshrc-crsh.gc.ca">fellowships@sshrc-crsh.gc.ca</a><br> <strong>Tel.:</strong>&nbsp;<a href="tel:613-943-7777">613-943-7777</a></p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#8f56e264-4356-4f68-9618-77f1b2dfbf35");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h2 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1508789013388-nserc-indigenous-student-ambassadors" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#7be531a2-71b1-47c4-bffb-6070de5cb2ab" href="#accordion-content-1508789013388-nserc-indigenous-student-ambassadors" aria-controls="accordion-content-1508789013388-nserc-indigenous-student-ambassadors" aria-expanded="false">
                            NSERC Indigenous Student Ambassadors
                        </a>
                    </h2>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1508789013388-nserc-indigenous-student-ambassadors" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1508789013388-nserc-indigenous-student-ambassadors">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1508789013388 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="41893e36-448b-4d1a-bb49-4d8ee0f64375" >

    <p>The NSERC Indigenous Student Ambassadors (NISA) grant aims to engage Indigenous students and fellows in promoting interest and participation in the natural sciences and engineering (NSE) by visiting Canada’s Indigenous communities and schools and sharing their research and education experiences or participating in science promotion events and activities.</p> 
<p>To be eligible, you must:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>be a Canadian citizen or permanent resident of Canada;</li> 
 <li>be an Indigenous person;<a href="http://www.nserc-crsng.gc.ca/students-etudiants/aboriginal-autochtones_eng.asp#note1" title="This link opens in a new window">*<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></li> 
 <li>be registered full-time in a degree program in the NSE at an eligible institution or be employed at an eligible institution as a postdoctoral fellow in the NSE at the time your application is submitted.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>* ‘Indigenous peoples’ is a collective name for the original peoples of North America and their descendants. ‘Aboriginal peoples’ is also often used as a synonym. For the purposes of this program, NSERC uses the Canadian&nbsp;<em>Constitution Act, 1982</em>&nbsp;definition of Aboriginal peoples as including the Indian, Inuit and Métis peoples of Canada.</p> 
<p><a href="http://www.nserc-crsng.gc.ca/students-etudiants/aboriginal-autochtones_eng.asp">Application details<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#41893e36-448b-4d1a-bb49-4d8ee0f64375");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
